Package com.deliveryCompany.components

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    Node
    Represents the location of a package, can refer to branches and trucks (all points where the package can be in the various stages of its transfer).
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    Address
    This class represents an address of a costumer (sender \ recipient)
    Branch
    Describes a local branch.
    Hub
    This class represents a hub branch - a branch that acts as a sorting center where all packages from local branches are sent to after initial collection.
    MainOffice
    This class represents a main office that creates the branches of the delivery company, the trucks for the branches and the packages and makes the whole system run according to a clock
    NonStandardPackage
    Represents the non-standard size packages.
    NonStandardTruck
    This class represents a non standard truck that collects and delivers non standard packages (one at a time)
    Package
    A general type represents packages.
    SmallPackage
    This class represents a small package
    StandardPackage
    Class represents packages with varying weights over one kilogram.
    StandardTruck
    Vehicle for transporting packages from the sorting center to the branches and back.
    Tracking
    This class represents Tracking listing of a package
    Truck
    Department representing the vehicles for transporting packages.
    Van
    This class represents a non standard truck that collects and delivers non standard packages (one at a time)
  • Enum Summary
    Enum Description
    Priority
    This enum is for setting the priority of a certain package shipment
    Status
    This enum is for setting the status of a certain package
